Sheet1.Comments:
The issue occurs if two conditions are satisfied in the same 5 ms cycle:
1. !BrakePedalApplied_K1 && BrakePedalApplied
2. pCmpF_SC > 3 bar

if this happens, the monitoring logic in class BSM_LeakageMonStateMachine ignores a robustness measure, which is to use the nominal stroke value at 3 bar as the staring stroke:
line 35 RecordedStrokeRising = InputRodStroke.max(MinStartStroke) yields the current InputRodStroke, since MinStartStroke is set to zero by line 25: self.init();

Since the current InputRodStroke can be rather small in case of fast pedal apply at low temperature with dynamic pressure effects, this leads to a high volume difference with the measured stroke at pedal release, which can in turn lead to a resulting leakage rate above the degradation threshold

